<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-4xl">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">How To Use Insaight Hub with AI Tools</h1>
  <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-8">Learn how to create and manage insights using AI assistants like Cursor or Claude Code through the Model Context Protocol (MCP).</p>

  <!-- Quick Setup Reference -->
  <div class="alert alert-info mb-8">
    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="stroke-current shrink-0 w-6 h-6"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
    <div>
      <p class="font-semibold">First time setup?</p>
      <p>Visit your <%= link_to "Profile", profile_path, class: "link link-primary" %> to get your personalized MCP configuration snippet. One config works for all your organizations &mdash; the AI will ask which org to use. Insaight Hub supports OAuth authentication, so your MCP client will prompt you to sign in via your browser on first use.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Claude Code Auto-Setup -->
  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl mb-8">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title text-xl">Quick Setup for Claude Code</h2>
      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-4">Copy this prompt and paste it into Claude Code to set up the MCP connection automatically:</p>

      <div class="relative" data-controller="clipboard">
        <div class="mockup-code mb-2">
          <pre data-prefix=">" class="text-success" data-clipboard-target="source"><code>Add an MCP server called "insaight-hub" to my project settings. The URL is <%= request.base_url %>/mcp and the transport is http. Use the OAuth configuration (no API token needed).</code></pre>
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-xs absolute top-2 right-2 bg-neutral border-none shadow-none text-neutral-content hover:bg-white hover:text-primary" data-action="clipboard#copy" data-clipboard-target="button" title="Copy to clipboard">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-base-content/50">For Cursor or manual setup, visit your <%= link_to "Profile", profile_path, class: "link link-primary" %> for JSON config snippets.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Available Tools -->
  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl mb-8">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title text-xl">Available MCP Tools</h2>
      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-4">Once connected, your AI assistant will have access to these tools:</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="table table-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Tool</th>
              <th>Description</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="font-mono text-sm">list_organizations</td><td>List all organizations you belong to</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono text-sm">list_insights</td><td>List insights with optional filtering (accepts <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">organization</code> param)</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono text-sm">get_insight</td><td>Get details of a specific insight by slug (returns markdown by default, or raw HTML with <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">format: "html"</code>)</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono text-sm">create_insight</td><td>Create a new insight with content (accepts <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">organization</code> param)</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono text-sm">update_insight</td><td>Update an existing insight's content or metadata</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono text-sm">publish_insight</td><td>Publish a draft insight</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono text-sm">unpublish_insight</td><td>Unpublish an insight back to draft</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono text-sm">delete_insight</td><td>Delete an insight</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono text-sm">move_insight</td><td>Move an insight from one organization to another</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="font-mono text-sm">get_tags</td><td>Get all available tags for an organization</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Example 1: Create and Publish -->
  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl mb-8">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title text-xl">
        <span class="badge badge-primary badge-lg mr-2">Example 1</span>
        Creating and Publishing an Insight
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-4">
        Ask your AI assistant to create a new insight. Here's an example prompt you can use:
      </p>

      <div class="relative" data-controller="clipboard">
        <div class="mockup-code mb-4">
          <pre data-prefix=">" class="text-success" data-clipboard-target="source"><code>Create an insight titled "Docker Best Practices" for developers. Include tips about multi-stage builds, layer caching, and security. Tag it with "docker", "devops", and "containers".</code></pre>
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-xs absolute top-2 right-2 bg-neutral border-none shadow-none text-neutral-content hover:bg-white hover:text-primary" data-action="clipboard#copy" data-clipboard-target="button" title="Copy to clipboard">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>

      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-4">
        The AI will use the <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">create_insight</code> tool with these parameters:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm mb-4 ml-4">
        <li><strong>title</strong>: "Docker Best Practices"</li>
        <li><strong>audience</strong>: "developer"</li>
        <li><strong>tags</strong>: ["docker", "devops", "containers"]</li>
        <li><strong>content</strong>: The generated HTML content</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="divider">Then publish it</div>

      <div class="relative" data-controller="clipboard">
        <div class="mockup-code mb-4">
          <pre data-prefix=">" class="text-success" data-clipboard-target="source"><code>Now publish the Docker Best Practices insight.</code></pre>
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-xs absolute top-2 right-2 bg-neutral border-none shadow-none text-neutral-content hover:bg-white hover:text-primary" data-action="clipboard#copy" data-clipboard-target="button" title="Copy to clipboard">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>

      <p class="text-base-content/70">
        The AI will use the <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">publish_insight</code> tool with the insight's slug to make it visible to everyone.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Example 2: Read and Build From an Insight -->
  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl mb-8">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title text-xl">
        <span class="badge badge-secondary badge-lg mr-2">Example 2</span>
        Reading an Insight to Create a PRD
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-4">
        Insights are returned in markdown by default, making them easy for AI to read and build on. Here's an example that reads an existing insight and uses it as the basis for a product requirements document:
      </p>

      <div class="relative" data-controller="clipboard">
        <div class="mockup-code mb-4">
          <pre data-prefix=">" class="text-success" data-clipboard-target="source"><code>Read the "api-rate-limiting-research" insight from Insaight Hub, then use it to write a PRD for implementing rate limiting in our API. Include the requirements, acceptance criteria, and technical approach.</code></pre>
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-xs absolute top-2 right-2 bg-neutral border-none shadow-none text-neutral-content hover:bg-white hover:text-primary" data-action="clipboard#copy" data-clipboard-target="button" title="Copy to clipboard">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>

      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-4">
        The AI will use <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">get_insight</code> to fetch the content as clean markdown, then use that context to draft your PRD. This works great for turning research notes, meeting summaries, or technical spikes into actionable documents.
      </p>

      <div class="alert mt-4">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="stroke-info shrink-0 w-6 h-6"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
        <span><strong>Tip:</strong> Insights are returned as markdown by default, so the AI can read and reason about them without parsing raw HTML. Use <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">format: "html"</code> if you need the original files.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Example 3: Update an Insight -->
  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl mb-8">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title text-xl">
        <span class="badge badge-accent badge-lg mr-2">Example 3</span>
        Updating an Existing Insight
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-4">
        You can ask your AI to modify existing insights. Here's an example:
      </p>

      <div class="relative" data-controller="clipboard">
        <div class="mockup-code mb-4">
          <pre data-prefix=">" class="text-success" data-clipboard-target="source"><code>Update my "docker-best-practices" insight to add a section about Docker Compose best practices. Also add the "docker-compose" tag to it.</code></pre>
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-xs absolute top-2 right-2 bg-neutral border-none shadow-none text-neutral-content hover:bg-white hover:text-primary" data-action="clipboard#copy" data-clipboard-target="button" title="Copy to clipboard">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>

      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-4">
        The AI will first use <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">get_insight</code> to fetch the current content, then use <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">update_insight</code> to modify it:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm mb-4 ml-4">
        <li><strong>slug</strong>: "docker-best-practices"</li>
        <li><strong>tags</strong>: ["docker", "devops", "containers", "docker-compose"]</li>
        <li><strong>files</strong>: Updated content with the new section</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Example 4: Multi-file Insight -->
  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl mb-8">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title text-xl">
        <span class="badge badge-neutral badge-lg mr-2">Example 4</span>
        Creating a Multi-File Insight
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-4">
        For more complex insights, you can include multiple files like HTML, CSS, and JavaScript:
      </p>

      <div class="relative" data-controller="clipboard">
        <div class="mockup-code mb-4">
          <pre data-prefix=">" class="text-success" data-clipboard-target="source"><code>Create an interactive insight called "CSS Grid Playground" for developers. Include an HTML file with examples, a CSS file with the grid styles, and a JavaScript file for interactivity.</code></pre>
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-xs absolute top-2 right-2 bg-neutral border-none shadow-none text-neutral-content hover:bg-white hover:text-primary" data-action="clipboard#copy" data-clipboard-target="button" title="Copy to clipboard">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>

      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-4">
        The AI will create the insight with multiple files, all bundled together and viewable as an interactive page.
      </p>

      <div class="alert mt-4">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="stroke-info shrink-0 w-6 h-6"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
        <span><strong>Tip:</strong> For larger multi-file insights (more than 3 files), the AI will automatically create the entry file first, then add remaining files in batches to stay within request size limits.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Example 5: Multi-Organization -->
  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl mb-8">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title text-xl">
        <span class="badge badge-info badge-lg mr-2">Example 5</span>
        Working with Multiple Organizations
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-4">
        If you belong to multiple organizations, the AI will ask which one to use. You can also specify it directly:
      </p>

      <div class="relative" data-controller="clipboard">
        <div class="mockup-code mb-4">
          <pre data-prefix=">" class="text-success" data-clipboard-target="source"><code>List my organizations in Insaight Hub.</code></pre>
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-xs absolute top-2 right-2 bg-neutral border-none shadow-none text-neutral-content hover:bg-white hover:text-primary" data-action="clipboard#copy" data-clipboard-target="button" title="Copy to clipboard">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>

      <p class="text-base-content/70 mb-4">Then create an insight in a specific org:</p>

      <div class="relative" data-controller="clipboard">
        <div class="mockup-code mb-4">
          <pre data-prefix=">" class="text-success" data-clipboard-target="source"><code>Create an insight titled "Q1 Roadmap" for stakeholders in the "Acme Corp" organization.</code></pre>
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-xs absolute top-2 right-2 bg-neutral border-none shadow-none text-neutral-content hover:bg-white hover:text-primary" data-action="clipboard#copy" data-clipboard-target="button" title="Copy to clipboard">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>

      <div class="divider">Moving insights between organizations</div>

      <div class="relative" data-controller="clipboard">
        <div class="mockup-code mb-4">
          <pre data-prefix=">" class="text-success" data-clipboard-target="source"><code>Move the "docker-best-practices" insight from "Personal" to "Acme Corp".</code></pre>
        </div>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-xs absolute top-2 right-2 bg-neutral border-none shadow-none text-neutral-content hover:bg-white hover:text-primary" data-action="clipboard#copy" data-clipboard-target="button" title="Copy to clipboard">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z" />
          </svg>
        </button>
      </div>

      <p class="text-base-content/70">
        The AI uses <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">list_organizations</code> to discover your orgs, then passes the organization name to tools like <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">create_insight</code> and <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">move_insight</code>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Tips Section -->
  <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-xl">
    <div class="card-body">
      <h2 class="card-title text-xl">Tips for Best Results</h2>

      <ul class="space-y-3 mt-4">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary font-bold">1.</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Be specific about your audience</strong>
            <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">Choose from: <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">developer</code>, <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">stakeholder</code>, or <code class="bg-base-200 px-1 rounded">end_user</code></p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary font-bold">2.</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Use descriptive tags</strong>
            <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">Tags help organize and find insights later. Use lowercase, hyphenated names.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary font-bold">3.</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Ask to list your insights first</strong>
            <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">If you're not sure of an insight's slug, ask the AI to list your insights.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary font-bold">4.</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Review before publishing</strong>
            <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">Insights are created as drafts by default. Review them before publishing.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-primary font-bold">5.</span>
          <div>
            <strong>One MCP config for all organizations</strong>
            <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">You don't need separate MCP configs per org. The AI will ask which organization to use, or you can specify it in your prompt.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
